result.execSummary:
The defendant Marco A Castillo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Graffiti [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.017(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: REQUEST TO ISSUE CIVIL JUDGMENT FOR RESTITUTION RECEIVED AND FORWARDED TO ALI. OS
Amended per restitution ordered.

Attorney Patrick Dennis Wait in court.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The defendant's appearance was previously waived.  Restitution hearing proceeded.  Arguments heard.  As a condition of probation, Court ordered restitution set at $576.60 to be paid to the City of Franklin or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Court ordered restitution set at $0.00 as to Sentry Foods.  The State was unable to provide information as to the co-defendants due to them being charged as juveniles.

Defendant Marco A Castillo in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any other sentence;  Huber privileges for school and work.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.
Conditions: 
*  Remain in school;
*  Pay restitution in an amount to be determined; jointly and severally;
*  Possess no alcohol/drugs.

Court orders all costs and surcharges waived due to the defendant's inability to pay.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.  Restitution hearing scheduled for April 1, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Marco A Castillo in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court granted state's motion for adjournment of sentencing to allow victim to be notified.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 21.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for February 18, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Marco A Castillo in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Parties are advised that effective December 14, 2015, this case will be assigned to the Reserve Judge presiding in Branch 21 in room 622 of the Courthouse.  Jury trial scheduled for February 22, 2016 at 08:30 am.  Final pre-trial scheduled for February 2, 2016 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Marco A Castillo in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin with student intern Daniel Murphy.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 24.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 19, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Marco A Castillo in court with attorney Patrick Dennis Wait.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defense counsel is unable to locate his file.  Court ordered case adjourned for pretrial conference in Branch 24.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 12, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference in Branch 24.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 18, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Court will withdraw the Arrest Warrant issued on 2-2-2015.  Defendant has pending matter in Branch 38, 14CM4753.   
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Atty Wait will contact SPD for appointment to this case.
Case is adjourned to 5-6-2015 at 8:15 for plea/sentencing.
Court will release defendant without bail.
